  "text": "The Mozilla Firefox CSS layout engine reflow pipeline is implemented across multiple interconnected C++ components in the layout module:\n\n## Frame Construction (layout/base/)\nThe frame construction process is coordinated by nsCSSFrameConstructor (nsCSSFrameConstructor.cpp/h and nsFrameManager.cpp/h). The nsCSSFrameConstructor class manages the creation of the frame tree that mirrors the DOM content tree. The ConstructRootFrame() method is the entry point for creating the root frame of the document, and nsFrameConstructorState manages construction state during this process.\n\n## Reflow Pipeline Orchestration (layout/base/)\nThe PresShell (PresShell.cpp/h) coordinates the overall reflow process. The ProcessReflowCommands() method is the main entry point that processes all dirty frames marked for reflow. PresShellForwards.h defines key enums like IntrinsicDirty and ReflowRootHandling that control how frames are marked for reflow. The nsPresContext (nsPresContext.cpp/h) maintains presentation context state, and nsRefreshDriver (nsRefreshDriver.cpp/h) coordinates refresh cycles where reflows occur.\n\n## Reflow Input/Output (layout/generic/)\nReflowInput (ReflowInput.cpp/h) encapsulates the parameters needed for reflow, including available space, intrinsic size computations, and containing block dimensions. ReflowOutput (ReflowOutput.cpp/h) holds the results of a reflow operation, containing metrics like desired size and overflow areas.\n\n## Block Layout Reflow (layout/generic/)\nThe nsBlockFrame (nsBlockFrame.cpp/h) implements reflow for block-level layout. BlockReflowState (BlockReflowState.cpp/h) manages state during block reflow including margins, borders, padding, and floats. nsBlockReflowContext (nsBlockReflowContext.cpp/h) provides utilities for reflowing block children and handling float management through nsFloatManager (nsFloatManager.cpp/h).\n\n## Dirty Frame Invalidation (layout/generic/ and layout/base/)\nThe DepthOrderedFrameList (DepthOrderedFrameList.cpp/h) maintains the list of dirty root frames that need reflow, organized by depth to ensure proper processing order. nsFrameState (nsFrameState.cpp/h) manages frame state bits that track whether frames are dirty or have other state flags. nsAutoLayoutPhase (nsAutoLayoutPhase.cpp/h) manages reflow phase tracking to ensure proper invalidation sequencing.\n\n## Core Frame Interface (layout/generic/)\nnsIFrame (nsIFrame.cpp/h) is the base frame class that defines the Reflow() virtual method called for all frame types. nsContainerFrame (nsContainerFrame.cpp/h) extends nsIFrame for frames that contain children. nsLineLayout (nsLineLayout.cpp/h) and nsLineBox (nsLineBox.cpp/h) handle inline-level layout within lines.\n\n## Supporting Infrastructure\nnsLayoutUtils (nsLayoutUtils.cpp/h) provides utility functions for layout calculations. nsSplittableFrame (nsSplittableFrame.cpp/h) handles frame continuations for pagination and column layout. AbsoluteContainingBlock (AbsoluteContainingBlock.cpp/h) manages absolute positioning. nsFrameList (nsFrameList.cpp/h) manages frame hierarchy. The OverflowChangedTracker (OverflowChangedTracker.h) tracks overflow changes during reflow.\n\nThe complete reflow pipeline flow is: ProcessReflowCommands() → ConstructRootFrame() (for construction) → nsIFrame::Reflow() → nsBlockFrame::Reflow() (for block layout) with dirty frame tracking through DepthOrderedFrameList and frame state bits managed in nsFrameState."
}

